President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Scott O'Malia as Commissioner of the Commodities Futures Trading Commission. O'Malia currently serves as the Minority Clerk of the Senate Subcommittee on Energy and Water Development. He has focused on expanding US investment in clean energy technologies and enhancing domestic oil and gas production. O'Malia has also worked in the corporate sector, establishing rules and standards for corporate risk management and energy trading. He began his career on Capitol Hill in 1992 and holds a bachelor's degree from the University of Michigan.